🔍 *Check Installed RU and Patches*

To find out which RU and patches are installed in each Oracle Home, use the opatch lsinventory command. This command will list the installed patches, including their versions. If any recommended patch of the correct version is already installed, you don't need to replace it. This check is particularly relevant for CLIENT homes.

*Example:*

1. Switch to the Oracle user:
   
   su - oracle
   

2. Set the Oracle Home environment variable:
   
   export ORACLE_HOME=/u01/oracle/product/19/db
   

3. Run the command to list installed patches:
   
   $ $ORACLE_HOME/OPatch/opatch lsinventory | grep -e Home -e applied -e description
   

   *Output:*
   
   Oracle Home       : /u01/oracle/product/19/db
   ARU platform description:: Linux x86-64
   There are 1 products installed in this Oracle Home.
   .
   .
   Patch  30894985     : applied on Fri Aug 21 12:47:55 CDT 2020
   Patch description:  "OCW RELEASE UPDATE 19.7.0.0.0 (30894985)"
   Patch  30869156     : applied on Fri Aug 21 12:45:41 CDT 2020
   Patch description:  "Database Release Update : 19.7.0.0.200414 (30869156)"
   

Use this information to determine if any updates or patches need to be applied.

