🔧 *Install OPatch 12.2.0.1.30*

Oracle recommends updating to the latest OPatch version for optimal performance. Make sure to update the OPatch utility in all Oracle software homes being patched.

*Note:* You can install OPatch while systems are online—no need to shut down the grid, database, or client homes.

Ensure the OPatch version is consistent across all Oracle RAC database homes and the Grid home.

*Steps to Update OPatch:*

1. *Check Current OPatch Version:*

   
   su - oracle
   whoami # should return oracle
   export ORACLE_HOME=/u01/oracle/product/19/db
   

2. *Backup Current OPatch:*

   
   cd $ORACLE_HOME
   mv OPatch OPatch_old1
   

3. *Install New OPatch:*

   
   cd <stage>
   unzip p6880880_200000_*.zip -d $ORACLE_HOME
   

This will update OPatch to the latest version, ensuring consistency and compatibility across your Oracle environments. ✅

