🔍 *Check for Open Files* 🔍

All files in the RDBMS or CLIENT Oracle Homes that you intend to patch on this server should be closed. The opatchauto command requires GRID to be started, so files in the GRID home will be open at this time. The opatchauto command will stop and start GRID. TFA should not be running.

If the lsof utility is installed, it can be used to determine if there are open files. The lsof utility might only be installed when Linux is installed. If lsof is not available, use an available utility or continue.

*Examples*:

su - root
lsof | grep -e COMMAND -e /u01/oracle/product/19/db

