🚀 *Execute Datapatch* 🚀

Once all RDBMS homes for the primary and standby databases have been patched, execute Datapatch to complete the post-install SQL for all related patches. In a RAC environment, this may be performed with one or more open instances. Do not execute in STANDBY databases; this will be performed through redo apply at the Standby Site.

Datapatch must be executed for all databases that use the RDBMS home where the Database RU and other patches with post-install SQL requirements were applied.

*Commands*:

su - oracle
export ORACLE_HOME=/u01/oracle/product/19/db
export ORACLE_SID=<sid>
$ORACLE_HOME/OPatch/datapatch -verbose

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

✅ *Verify dba_registry_sqlpatch* ✅

Ensure that dba_registry_sqlpatch has been updated with the current Release Update patch 33515361. If it has not, proceed with the remainder of the process and open a service request with Oracle Support to investigate the issue with dba_registry_sqlpatch.

*Commands*:

su - oracle
export ORACLE_HOME=/u01/oracle/product/19/db
export ORACLE_SID=<sid>
$ORACLE_HOME/bin/sqlplus / as sysdba
Set linesize 132
select action, ACTION_TIME, PATCH_ID, STATUS from dba_registry_sqlpatch;
exit

