⚠ *Handle Invalid Objects* ⚠

If invalid objects exist, especially Oracle maintained objects, execute utlrp for all PDBs in the CDB.

*Commands*:

cd $ORACLE_HOME/rdbms/admin
$ORACLE_HOME/perl/bin/perl catcon.pl -n 1 -e -b utlrp -d '''.''' utlrp.sql

Check for invalid objects again after utlrp has been executed.

- If any non-Oracle maintained objects are invalid after the post-SQL tasks and were not invalid before, contact the object owners (e.g., Solution Works) to correct the issue.
- If any Oracle maintained objects are invalid after the post-SQL tasks, notify an Oracle database support group.

