🛠 Oracle Database Patching Steps 🛠

1. Check OPatch Version 🔍
   - Check the current version of the OPatch tool.
   - Upgrade the OPatch utility if needed.

2. Backup ORACLE_HOME 📦
   - Take a backup of the ORACLE_HOME directory.

3. Shutdown Services ⏹
   - Shutdown the Database and Listener running from the ORACLE_HOME to be patched.

4. Apply Patch 🔧
   - Apply the PSU patch on ORACLE_HOME.

5. Validate Patch ✅
   - Validate the applied patch in the inventory.

6. Post-Installation Steps 🚀
   - Execute post-installation steps using datapatch.

7. Restart Services 🔄
   - Startup the Database and Listener services associated with the patched ORACLE_HOME.

8. Verify Patch Status 📊
   - Verify the status of the applied patch from dba_registry_sqlpatch.

